info.title: Open Referral API
info.description: This is a specification describing the Open Referral API, using the Human Services Specification. This has been extracted from the Ohana API deployment, but will be standardized to refer to the universal standard that will apply to any Open Referral compliant API.

parameters.name: per_page
parameters.description: Amount of locations to return per page, up to 100.

parameters.name: country_prefix
parameters.description: The country prefix code, such as +1 for the USA.

parameters.name: per_page
parameters.description: Amount of locations to return per page, up to 100.

parameters.name: accessibility
parameters.description: Accessibility options available at the location. Accepted values are cd, deaf_interpreter, disabled_parking, elevator, ramp, restroom, tape_braille, tty, wheelchair, and wheelchair_van.

parameters.name: address_attributes
parameters.description: required unless the location is marked as virtual

parameters.name: admin_emails
parameters.description: Email address for a person allowed to administer the location (via the Ohana API Admin interface for example).

parameters.name: alternate_name
parameters.description: Another name this location might be known by.

parameters.name: description
parameters.description: Description of services provided at the location

parameters.name: email
parameters.description: General Email address for location. Emails that belong to contacts should go in the Contact object.

parameters.name: latitude
parameters.description: Latitude portion of the location’s coordinates. Note that the app automatically geocodes addresses if the data doesn’t include coordinates

parameters.name: longitude
parameters.description: Longitude portion of the location’s coordinates. Note that the app automatically geocodes addresses if the data doesn’t include coordinates

parameters.name: short_desc
parameters.description: Succinct description of services provided at the location.

parameters.name: transportation
parameters.description: Public transportation options near the location

parameters.name: virtual
parameters.description: required if the location does not have a physical address

parameters.name: website
parameters.description: The location’s website. Must include “http://” or “https://”

get.summary: Get locations that match certain criteria.
get.description: Get locations that match certain criteria.
